Special thanks to thn81, L42y, City-Busz, and all of the other AUR maintainers that helped make it possible to run Unity under Arch Linux!

Please make sure you don't already have modified versions of the dependencies installed. For example, gtk3-ubuntu might fail to compile if there's a modified version of gtk3 already installed.

Packages ending with "-ubuntu" contain Ubuntu patches and REPLACE Arch Linux versions of those packages.

Order to compile/install:

01: glib2-ubuntu                   -> glib 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
02: gtk2-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
03: gtk3-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 3.0 with Ubuntu patches
04: qt-ubuntu                      -> Qt toolkit with Ubuntu patches
05: gconf-ubuntu                   -> A configuration database system
06: libdbusmenu                    -> Library for passing menus over DBus
07: libindicator                   -> Symbols and functions for indicators
08: libindicate                    -> Libraries for apps to raise 'flags' on DBus
09: libindicate-qt                 -> Qt bindings for libindicate
10: libappindicator                -> Library to export menu bar to Unity
11: appmenu-gtk                    -> Application menu module for GTK+
12: bamf                           -> Application matching framework
13: libqtbamf                      -> Qt bindings for bamf
14: dee                            -> Create Model-View-Controller apps over DBus
15: libqtdee                       -> Qt binding and QML plugin for Dee
16: libqtgconf                     -> Qt bindings for GConf
17: dconf-qt                       -> Qt bindings for DConf
18: sni-qt                         -> Turns Qt tray icons into appindicators
19: ido                            -> Widgets and objects used for indicators
20: libzeitgeist                   -> Client library to interact with Zeitgeist
21: zeitgeist-datahub              -> Plugins that insert events into Zeitgeist
22: python2-geoclue                 -> Geoclue Python module
23: python2-xapian                  -> Python bindings for Xapian
24: zeitgeist-extensions           -> Extensions for Zeitgeist
25: gnome-activity-journal         -> Tool for easily browsing and finding files
26: gsettings-desktop-schemas-ubuntu -> Shared GSettings schemas for the desktop
27: gnome-settings-daemon-ubuntu   -> Daemon handling the GNOME session settings
28: gnome-session-ubuntu           -> GNOME Session Manager
29: pulseaudio-ubuntu              -> A featureful, general-purpose sound server
30: gnome-control-center-ubuntu    -> Utilities to configure the GNOME desktop
31: gnome-screensaver-ubuntu       -> Screensaver and screen locking for GNOME
32: metacity-ubuntu                -> Lightweight GTK+ window manager
33: launchpad-integration          -> Launchpad.net integration
34: indicator-applet               -> GNOME panel indicator applet
35: indicator-application          -> Takes menus and puts then in the panel
36: indicator-appmenu              -> An indicator to host the menus from apps
37: libtimezonemap                 -> GTK+3 timezone map widget
38: indicator-datetime             -> A very, very simple clock
39: indicator-messages             -> Collects messages that need a response
40: indicator-multiload            -> Port of the GNOME multiload applet
41: indicator-power                -> Indicator to show battery information
42: indicator-session              -> Indicator to manage session
43: indicator-sound                -> A unified sound menu
44: network-manager-applet-ubuntu  -> Network Manager applet with indicator support
45: gnome-bluetooth-ubuntu         -> Gnome bluetooth applet with indicator support
46: gtest                          -> C++ testing utility based on xUnit
47: gmock                          -> A library for writing C++ mock classes
48: overlay-scrollbar *            -> Overlay scrollbars for GTK 2 and GTK 3
49: plasma-widget-menubar *        -> KDE Plasma widget to display menubar
50: xfce4-indicator-plugin *       -> XFCE panel plugin to display indicators
51: utouch-evemu                   -> Event emulation for the uTouch stack
52: utouch-frame                   -> Touch frame library
53: fixesproto-ubuntu              -> X11 Fixes extension wire protocol
54: libxfixes-ubuntu               -> X11 misc. 'fixes' extension library
55: xorg-server-ubuntu             -> Xorg X server
56: check                          -> Unit testing framework for C
57: utouch-grail                   -> Gesture recognition and instantiation lib.
58: utouch-geis                    -> Implementation of the GEIS interface
59: nux                            -> An OpenGL toolkit
60: unity-asset-pool               -> Design assets for Unity
61: gnome-menus2                   -> Gnome menu specifications
62: libunity                       -> Library for integrating Unity
63: libunity-misc                  -> Differently licensed stuff for Unity
64: nautilus-ubuntu                -> File manager and graphics shell for GNOME
65: unity-lens-applications        -> Unity applications lens
66: unity-lens-files               -> Unity files lens
67: unity-lens-music               -> Unity music lens
68: unity-lens-video               -> Unity video lens
69: compiz-core-ubuntu             -> Compiz core components
70: libcompizconfig-ubuntu         -> Compiz configuration system library
71: compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu * -> GConf backend for Compiz
72: compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu * -> KConfig4 backend for Compiz
73: compizconfig-python-ubuntu     -> Compizconfig bindings for Python
74: ccsm-ubuntu                    -> Compiz configuration manager
75: compiz-plugins-main-ubuntu     -> Compiz main plugins
76: compiz-plugins-extra-ubuntu    -> Compiz extra plugins
77: unity-core *                   -> Parts of Unity 3D needed for Unity 2D
78: unity                          -> A desktop experience designed for efficiency
79: unity-2d                       -> 2D implementation of Unity

* Optional packages
  - overlay-scrollbar              => For GNOME/Unity users who want a space saving scrollbar
  - plasma-widget-menubar          => For KDE users who want a global menubar
  - xfce4-indicator-plugin         => Ayatana indicators plugin for the XFCE panel
  - compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in GConf
  - compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in KConfig4
  - unity-core                     => For users that want Unity 2D, but not Unity 3D

All of PKGBUILD's were checked by namcap for consistency. The binary packages have not been checked yet.

Troubleshooting:

Global menus aren't working when logging in with KDM (KDE display manager).

  This happens because previous versions of KDM weren't patched to source the
  /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc.d/ directory. This is fixed in kdebase-workspace version
  4.7.2-1, but requires the KDM configuration files to be regenerated (resetting
  all KDM configuration options). To regenerate the configuration files, run as root

    # rm -rvf /usr/share/config/kdm
    # genkdmconf

AHH! Something is wrong with Unity!

  Try resetting the settings for Unity and Compiz and relogin:

    $ rm -rvf ~/.compiz-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.cache/compizconfig-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.config/compiz-1/
    $ gconftool-2 --recursive-unset /apps/compiz-1
    $ gconftool-2 --recursive-unset /apps/compizconfig-1
    $ rm -rvf ~/.gconf/apps/compiz-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.gconf/apps/compizconfig-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.cache/unity/
    $ rm -vf ~/.cache/unity-lens-video

  If something is still wrong, please file a bug report at either:

    https://github.com/chenxiaolong/Unity-for-Arch/issues

  or

    https://bugs.launchpad.net/unity-for-arch

I have an ATI graphics card that needs the AMD Catalyst/fglrx driver.

  Use the xorg-server-ubuntu-1.11 package instead of xorg-server-ubuntu.
